<h2>What is Simple Procedure?</h2>

<p>
<strong>Simple Procedure</strong> is Scotland's streamlined court process for civil claims up to <strong>£5,000</strong>. It replaced Small Claims in 2016 and is designed to be accessible without needing a solicitor.
</p>

<h3>Key Features:</h3>
<ul>
  <li>✅ <strong>Lower costs:</strong> Court fees range from £21 to £145</li>
  <li>✅ <strong>Informal hearings:</strong> The sheriff manages the case and helps both parties</li>
  <li>✅ <strong>No need for a solicitor:</strong> You can represent yourself (known as a "party litigant")</li>
  <li>✅ <strong>Faster resolution:</strong> Most cases are decided within 3-6 months</li>
</ul>

<p>
<strong>⚠️ IMPORTANT:</strong> If your claim exceeds £5,000, you must raise an Ordinary Cause action instead. Seek legal advice.
</p>

