<h2>If the Defender Does Not Respond (Decree by Default)</h2>

<p>
If the defender does not lodge a Response Form within 21 days, you can apply for <strong>decree by default</strong>. This means the sheriff will grant judgment in your favour without a hearing.
</p>

<h3>How to Apply for Decree by Default:</h3>

<ol>
  <li>Wait until the 21-day response period has expired.</li>
  <li>Write to the Sheriff Clerk stating:
    <blockquote>
    "I am the claimant in case [case reference number]. The defender has not lodged a response within the prescribed period. I respectfully request that the sheriff grant decree by default in terms of the sum claimed, namely {{currency total_claim_amount}} plus court fee of {{currency court_fee}} and expenses."
    </blockquote>
  </li>
  <li>The sheriff will review the file and, if satisfied, grant decree (usually within 7-14 days).</li>
  <li>You will receive a <strong>certified copy of the decree</strong> by post.</li>
</ol>

<hr>

<h2>After You Get Decree (Judgment)</h2>

<p>
If the defender does not pay voluntarily after decree is granted, you can enforce the judgment using:
</p>

<h3>Enforcement Options (Diligence) in Scotland:</h3>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Charge for Payment</strong> — A formal demand giving the defender 14 days to pay before further diligence</li>
  <li><strong>Earnings Arrestment</strong> — Deduct money from the defender's wages</li>
  <li><strong>Bank Arrestment</strong> — Freeze money in the defender's bank account</li>
  <li><strong>Attachment</strong> — Seize and sell the defender's belongings (via sheriff officers)</li>
  <li><strong>Inhibition</strong> — Prevent the defender from selling property they own</li>
</ul>

<p>
<strong>Note:</strong> You must first serve a <strong>Charge for Payment</strong> before using any other enforcement method (except inhibition).
</p>

<p>
<strong>Sheriff Officers:</strong> Most enforcement requires instructing sheriff officers (the Scottish equivalent of bailiffs). You will need to pay their fees upfront, but you can recover these from the defender if enforcement is successful.
</p>

