<h2>Do You Need a Solicitor?</h2>

<p>
<strong>No.</strong> Simple Procedure is designed so you can represent yourself without a solicitor.
</p>

<p>
However, you may wish to instruct a solicitor if:
</p>

<ul>
  <li>The defender lodges a complex defence;</li>
  <li>The claim involves legal arguments (e.g., interpretation of the tenancy agreement);</li>
  <li>You are not confident presenting your case at a hearing.</li>
</ul>

<p>
If you do instruct a solicitor, <strong>you may be able to recover their fees as expenses</strong> if you win, but this is not guaranteed. Check with your solicitor first.
</p>

